label.value: obsolete BG-Sentinel trap

definition.value: An arthropod trap that is manufactured by Biogents and is designed to attract arthropods through the use of a motorized fan to mimic convection currents produced by a human. The current also pulls arthropods into the trap, where a layer of gauze prevents the arthropods from escaping along with the air current.

label.value: obsolete barrier trap

definition.value: An arthropod trap consisting of a static physical barrier designed to funnel arthropods in flight into a container.

label.value: obsolete Onderstepoort Veterinary Institute light-suction trap

definition.value: A light trap that is designed to use motorized suction to trap arthropods in a collection bag once they approach the attractant. The light is supplied by an 8 watt tube, and the fan providing the suction has an 11-centimeter diameter.

label.value: obsolete resting box trap

definition.value: An arthropod trap that consists of a box that is open on one end. The placement of the box and modifications to it are done in such a way that it becomes attractive to an arthropod as a place to rest during a period of inactivity.

label.value: obsolete Shannon trap

definition.value: An arthropod trap that is made of cloth and netting and is designed to be suspended from above (e.g. from a tree). It is also designed so that the arthropod enters the trap from beneath, being attracted to some bait, and is prevented from escaping upward by the suspended cloth, which allows them to be collected from the upper interior of the trap.

label.value: obsolete sticky trap

definition.value: An arthropod trap that is designed to capture arthropods resting on a surface by coating the surface with adhesive.

label.value: obsolete artificial pit shelter

definition.value: An arthropod trap, consisting of a pit dug under the shelter of a plant, designed to provide a space for arthropods to rest and be collected.

label.value: obsolete resting bucket

definition.value: An arthropod trap that consists of a bucket, which is lined with fabric and placed on its side, and a wet cloth inside the bucket. The placement of the box and modifications to it are done in such a way that it becomes attractive to an arthropod as a place to rest during a period of inactivity.

label.value: obsolete Mosquito Magnet trap

definition.value: An arthropod trap that is powered by propane and is designed to emit a combination of carbon dioxide, heat, water, and oct-1-en-3-ol attractants while simultaneously using suction to trap arthropods.

label.value: obsolete knockdown arthropod specimen collection process

definition.value: An arthropod specimen collection process that involves exposing arthropods to pesticide, then collecting them once they become dead or immobilized.

label.value: obsolete MosquiTRAP

definition.value: A gravid trap consisting of an arthropod attractant and adhesive surface.

label.value: obsolete sticky resting bucket

definition.value: An arthropod trap that consists of a bucket, which is lined with adhesive and placed on its side, and a wet cloth inside the bucket. The placement of the box and modifications to it are done in such a way that it becomes attractive to an arthropod as a place to rest during a period of inactivity. The trap is designed for arthropods to become caught in the adhesive so that they can be collected.

label.value: obsolete light trap for indoor use

definition.value: A light trap designed to be placed inside a building.

label.value: obsolete knockdown arthropod specimen collection by pyrethrum spray

definition.value: A knockdown arthropod specimen collection process in which the pesticide is pyrethrum.

label.value: obsolete light trap

definition.value: An arthropod trap that uses light as an attractant.

label.value: obsolete live arthropod specimen collection process

definition.value: An arthropod specimen collection process meant to collect live specimens.

label.value: obsolete larval specimen collection process

definition.value: An arthropod specimen collection process in which the arthropods are in the larval stage.

label.value: obsolete daytime arthropod specimen collection by aspiration

definition.value: An arthropod specimen collection by aspiration that occurs in the daytime.

label.value: obsolete human-biting arthropod specimen collection by aspiration

definition.value: An arthropod specimen collection by aspiration that occurs while the arthropod is biting a human.

label.value: obsolete ovitrap

definition.value: An arthropod trap that consists of a container holding a mesh layer above water and is designed to trap arthropods hatched from eggs dropped over the water by gravid females.

label.value: obsolete human-biting indoor arthropod specimen collection by aspiration

definition.value: An arthropod specimen collection by aspiration that occurs while the arthropod is biting a human inside a building.

label.value: obsolete human-biting outdoor arthropod specimen collection by aspiration

definition.value: An arthropod specimen collection by aspiration designed to catch specimens that are in the process of biting a human outside a building.

label.value: obsolete arthropod specimen collection by aspiration

definition.value: A live arthropod specimen collection process that involves the use of an aspirator, a device which is brought to an arthropod and causes the arthropod to be drawn by suction into a container.

label.value: obsolete arthropod resting in animal house specimen collection by aspiration

definition.value: An arthropod specimen collection by aspiration that catches specimens resting inside an animal house.

label.value: obsolete arthropod resting outdoors specimen collection by aspiration

definition.value: An animal-biting arthropod specimen collection by aspiration that occurs while the arthropod is resting outside a building during a period of inactivity.

label.value: obsolete outlet window trap

definition.value: An arthropod trap that is positioned adjacent to a window of a building and is designed to collect arthropods flying out of the building.

label.value: obsolete adult arthropod specimen collection process

definition.value: A live arthropod specimen collection process in which the arthropods are in the adult stage.

label.value: obsolete animal-biting arthropod specimen collection by aspiration

definition.value: An arthropod specimen collection by aspiration that occurs while the arthropod is biting an animal.

label.value: obsolete arthropod resting outdoors on artificial support specimen collection by aspiration

definition.value: An arthropod resting outdoors specimen collection by aspiration that occurs while the arthropod rests on a processed material such as a wall or furniture.

label.value: obsolete light trap for outdoor use

definition.value: A light trap designed to be placed outside a building.

label.value: obsolete arthropod trap

definition.value: A device designed to catch arthropods.

label.value: obsolete arthropod specimen collection process

definition.value: A specimen collection process that has the objective of collecting arthropods as specimens.

label.value: obsolete animal-biting outdoor arthropod specimen collection by aspiration

definition.value: An animal-biting arthropod specimen collection by aspiration that occurs outside a building.

label.value: obsolete arthropod resting outdoors on natural support specimen collection by aspiration

definition.value: An arthropod resting outdoors specimen collection by aspiration that occurs while the arthropod rests on an unprocessed material such as a plant.

label.value: obsolete aquatic arthropod specimen collection process

definition.value: An arthropod specimen collection process that has the objective of collecting mosquitoes from an aquatic environment.

label.value: number of traps

definition.value: A count of the traps deployed in a study design execution.

label.value: obsolete landing arthropod specimen collection process

definition.value: An arthropod specimen collection process that occurs while the arthropods land on a surface.
For example, while they are landing on a human bait.

label.value: obsolete hand-held sweep net

definition.value: A device that consists of a network of mesh and is designed to capture adult arthropods.
Can be successfully used to catch resting or flying adult arthropods.  The net typically is mounted on a frame that is attached to a handle to increase the reach. [ISBN:9781402066658]

label.value: obsolete trap for emerging adult arthropods

definition.value: An arthropod trap that is designed to trap an arthropod as it emerges from water at the beginning of its adult stage.

label.value: obsolete Centers for Disease Control and Prevention gravid trap

definition.value: A gravid trap that consists of a pan holding a hay infusion, motorized fan, and collection bag. This trap is designed to attract gravid female arthropods to the infused material, which would serve as an oviposition medium, and then draw them into the bag with the current generated by the fan.

label.value: obsolete arthropod trap containing small non-human animal bait

definition.value: An arthropod trap that uses as attractant an animal that is not human and is the size of a chicken or smaller.
Small non-human animals used as bait include chickens and other birds, rabbits, rodents, and dogs.

label.value: obsolete dipper for arthropod immatures

definition.value: A device that is designed for the collection of arthropod larvae or pupae from water and has the shape of a ladle or a pan.

A dipper is a commonly used tool for collecting larvae and pupae from their aquatic development sites.  Dippers vary in size, shape and the material they are constructed from.  A variety of utensils have been used as dippers, e.g. soup ladles, rectangular enamel pie dishes, photographic trays, frying pans, plastic or enamel bowls, household metal strainers and spoons.  Volumes of water collected by the dipper can vary from 100 ml to more than 1 liter depending on the specific dipper used.  Dippers can be equipped with plastic or metal screen bottoms, or customized with long handles to increase their reach. [ISBN:9781402066658]"

label.value: obsolete resting flight-capable arthropod specimen collection process

definition.value: An arthropod specimen collection process that occurs while an arthropod that is capable of flight is resting outdoors during a period of inactivity.

label.value: obsolete free-standing window trap

definition.value: An arthropod trap that consists of a transparent window placed in a box that holds a liquid solution deadly to arthropods. This trap is designed to stop an arthropod in flight, causing it to fall into the liquid and die.

For example, Jonsson developed a free-standing window trap consisting of a 16 x 20-cm perspex box, 16 cm high and divided in the middle by a 20 x 36-cm sheet of perspex (window).  The two compartments of the box are filled to a depth of about 12 cm with 4-6% formalin containing a few drops of detergent; in winter ethylene glycol can be added to prevent freezing.  One or two holes drilled in one side of the box at 12 cm and covered with fine netting prevent the trap overflowing after heavy rain.  Traps are mounted on aluminium poles.  Flying insects on hitting the transparent vertical plastic window fall into the formalin.  The window trap may catch vectors that are seeking a host or moving for other purposes." [ISBN:9781402066658]

label.value: obsolete device for resting of adult arthropods for collection

definition.value: A device that is designed to provide a solid surface that is attractive to an arthropod as a place to rest during a period of inactivity.
Most commonly used to collect mosquitoes.

label.value: arthropod attractor

definition.value: A material entity that has an arthropod attractor role.

label.value: obsolete arthropod resting in human house specimen collection by aspiration

definition.value: An arthropod specimen collection by aspiration that catches specimens resting inside a human house.

label.value: obsolete baited net trap

definition.value: An arthropod trap designed to work with an animal (which could be human) inside a netted structure. This structure is designed so that an arthropod, attracted by the animal, can fly into the netted structure but can neither escape nor reach the animal.

label.value: infused material

definition.value: A processed material that results from the suspension of plant material in a solvent for enough time to allow compounds to be extracted from the plant material into the solvent.

label.value: obsolete pupal specimen collection process

definition.value: An arthropod specimen collection process in which the arthropods are in the pupal stage.
